{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"s:10GLibObject10TypePluginC","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypePlugin"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypePlugin","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"TypePlugin"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin"},"abstract":[{"text":"An interface that handles the lifecycle of dynamically loaded types.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeplugin"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TypePlugin","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The GObject type system supports dynamic loading of types."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It goes as follows:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type is initially introduced (usually upon loading the module"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the first time, or by your main application that knows what modules"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"introduces what types), like this:"}]},{"code":["new_type_id = g_type_register_dynamic (parent_type_id,","                                       \"TypeName\",","                                       new_type_plugin,","                                       type_flags);"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"text":" is an implementation of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" interface."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The type’s implementation is referenced, e.g. through","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeClass.ref"},{"type":"text","text":"] or through [func"},{"code":"GObject.type_create_instance","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(this is being called by [ctor","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.Object.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]) or through one of the above","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"done on a type derived from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_id"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This causes the type system to load the type’s implementation by calling","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.use","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At some point the type’s implementation isn’t required anymore, e.g. after"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeClass.unref"},{"text":"] or [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.type_free_instance","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(called when the reference count of an instance drops to zero).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This causes the type system to throw away the information retrieved","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info"},{"text":"] and then it calls","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.unuse"},{"text":"] on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Things may repeat from the second step."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"So basically, you need to implement a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" type that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"carries a use_count, once use_count goes from zero to one, you need","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to load the implementation to successfully handle the upcoming","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] call. Later, maybe after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"succeeding use\/unuse calls, once use_count drops to zero, you can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unload the implementation again. The type system makes sure to call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.use","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"again when the type is needed again.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","isActive":true},{"text":"] is an implementation of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"already implements most of this except for the actual module loading and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unloading. It even handles multiple registered types per module."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"}]}],"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentatio